# Node.js namespace imports

Always use namespace imports for Node.js built-in modules.

```typescript
// BAD — named imports lose module context at call sites
import { readFileSync, writeFileSync } from "node:fs";
import { join } from "node:path";
import { homedir } from "node:os";

readFileSync(path);
join(a, b);

// GOOD — namespace imports make call sites self-documenting
import * as fs from "node:fs";
import * as path from "node:path";
import * as os from "node:os";

fs.readFileSync(path);
path.join(a, b);
```
